Ahh! I see! This explains why California, with over twenty years experience of renewable power generation, enjoys abundant, inexpensive and reliable power supplies and indeed exports large amounts of electricity to her less enlightened neighbours whilst, By contrast, France, relying heavily on outdated, expensive and unreliable Nuclear generation has the most expensive electricity in the world, Suffers frequent brown-outs and power cuts and has to import heavily from her non-nuclear neighbours!<br>
