thousand times more distructive,. Then Other nations such<br>
as Soviet Russia did likewise. <br>
5. Then for 45 years the determination of both sides<br>
to avoid the mutual thermonuclear distruction of both sides<br>
if a war should occurr led them To keep the peace and settle their differences peacefully in the cold war, rather then fight World War 3 and blow up the whole world with H-bombs.<br>
6. If you really want to keep the peace between nations the surest, and most certian method of achieving this is for all the potentially warring  nations to be always armed to the the teeth with very many A-bombs, and H-bombs.<br>
7. If this occurrs it makes war so very distructuve, foolish,<br>
and sucidical for the all potential belligerents ,  because of M.A.D (mutual assured distruction) that they like the United<br>
States, and the Soviet Union did during the cold war will keep <br>
the peace, settle their differences peacefully, and avoid wars rather then fight them.<br>
8. Nuclear weapons  are thus  actually the surest , best, and<br>
most certian garuntee of the peace between nation for this reason.<br>
9. This nuclear weapon based approach is thus the most infallible method of preventing wars, and of keeping the peace <br>
between all sane, and rational nations, that have sane, and rational governments. , .. <br>
10. It is to maintain the nuclear balance of power,<br>
and the balance of terror which always keeps the peace.<br>
11.If you want live in freedom, and peace you must <br>
always prepare for all forms of war including for nuclear war.<br>
 12. This is peace through military strength alone,<br>
by means of military dterrence. In this way: The goal of Dr Gatling has been fully achieved by the development, and<br>
deployment of nuclear weapons around the world since 1945<br>
between the major national powers, and superpowers.<br>
.<br>
